[b][color=red][size=36pt]THE MAIN FIX[/size][/b]
Do a search on your hard drive for "rundll" (Start > Search) and you may get this:

[URL=http://img140.imageshack.us/i/prefetch.png/][IMG]http://img140.imageshack.us/img140/3797/prefetch.png[/img][/URL]

Notice the files I emphasised in red. They were last modified today, yesterday and a few days ago. Considering this and fact that the file name has .EXE AND it's in the prefetch cache, I'm dubbing these malicious [s]BUT please do not go deleting dlls until I confirm these to be malicious, I don't want to be deleting the wrong ones. Editing soon...[/s] Go to your C:/ Drive (or any other drive you use/have) and go to:

WINDOWS > Prefetch. 

Now, it's safe to delete the files from this folder as it's just a cache to load your previously opened applications much faster. If you have the rundll32.EXE.pf files, make sure to DELETE THESE IMMEDIATELY AND THEN EMPTY YOUR RECYCLE BIN. You may as well delete every file (CTRL + A > Delete > Enter) incase you miss one.

Now, regarding your client and/or server, if you want to go though every file and delete the malicious code, please do so, but if you miss something you'll be back to square one and be at major risk of being hacked. I suggest deleting these folders and reporting the poster immediately.

After this, run a clean-up on your computer (including Cookies and Temporary Internet Files) and then do a search on your hard drive again for "rundll". If you find nothing, I believe you are nearly safe, just one more thing to do.

Log on to RuneScape.com and change your password, PIN and secure your account up. Changing your password on RuneScape.com should be the LAST thing you do! If you do it before deleting the rundll's, you're still compromised and just risk giving the hacker your new password. Any questions? Just ask.
